                <head>333. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 5 at Ankara, the United States signed bilateral Agreements of
                    Cooperation with the Governments of Turkey, Iran, and Pakistan. These agreements
                    were developed pursuant to the July 28, 1958, declaration signed by the member
                    states of the Baghdad Pact at its Ministerial Meeting in London. The text of the
                    agreement with Turkey is in 10 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 320. For text
                    of a Department of State press release explaining the background of these
                    agreements, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, March 23,
                    1959, pages 416–417. For text of the July 28, 1958, declaration, see <hi
                        rend="italic">Ibid</hi>., August 18, 1958, pages 272–273.</p>
            </div>
